requests.name: Add private plugin
requests.description:
Adds or updates a private plugin.
A plugin exists as a repository in Github.
By adding a private plugin the plugin will appear on your settings -> plugins tab just like any other plugin which
can then be installed and/or added to a relay.
If a private plugin has the same name as an existing plugin it will override the existing plugin within your account.

queryParams.key:
plugin
Name of the plugin
org
Github organization or user owning the plugin
repo
Github repository name for plugin

requests.name: Remove private plugin

plugin disappear from available plugins in your settings.

queryParams.key:
plugin
Name of plugin to remove

requests.name: Available metrics
requests.description: Determine which metrics are available to return historical data for, for a specific subject (device or service) over a specific time range.

queryParams.description: Your API token
The ID of the subject to get the definitions for, e.g. a device ID.
The UTC date string for the start time range in format YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:SSZ e.g. 2013-09-15T00:00:00Z
The UTC date string for the end time range in format YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:SSZ e.g. 2013-09-15T23:59:59Z

requests.name: Dynamic metrics
requests.description: Return historical metrics data, for a devices and/or services that match a search or regex style inventory filter search over a specific time range.

queryParams.description: Your API token
A regular expression that will return all devices or services that match the pattern.
List of inventory IDs
Human-readable names of a device or service
The UTC date string for the start time range in format YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:SSZ e.g. 2013-09-15T00:00:00Z
The UTC date string for the end time range in format YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:SSZ e.g. 2013-09-15T23:59:59Z
Specify whether to return only devices, services or all.
